title: error: linking with `x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc`, undefined reference to `_Unwind_Resume'

labels.name: A-linkage
labels.description: Area: linking into static, shared libraries and binaries

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-stable
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another.

body:
Let me know if I should provide any more details, test anything out, or clarify anything. Also, note that I have tested many combinations of toolchain version + target + invocation type, but have not exhaustively tested every possible combination.

@rustbot modify labels: +regression-from-stable-to-stable +O-windows +O-windows-gnu +A-linkage

### Code

Literally anything, even an empty file or just a main function.

### Short error message

```
error: linking with `x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc` failed: exit code: 1
note: main.main.7rcbfp3g-cgu.3.rcgu.o:main.7rcbfp3g-cgu.:(.text+0x4c): undefined reference to `_Unwind_Resume'
```

### General version info

- `rustup 1.22.1 (b01adbbc3 2020-07-08)`
- `x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc (x86_64-posix-sjlj-rev0, Built by MinGW-W64 project) 8.1.0`
- Microsoft (R) Incremental Linker Version 14.27.29112.0
- Microsoft Windows 10 Home, 10.0.18363 Build 18363

### Version it worked on

`rustc 1.47.0 (18bf6b4f0 2020-10-07)` and `cargo 1.47.0 (f3c7e066a 2020-08-28)` (or earlier)

or

`x86_64-pc-windows-msvc`

or

`cargo build` without dependencies

or

`rustc` (without dependencies or anything)

### Version with regression

- `rustc 1.48.0 (7eac88abb 2020-11-16)` / `cargo 1.48.0 (65cbdd2dc 2020-10-14)` or
- `rustc 1.50.0-nightly (da3846948 2020-11-21)` / `cargo 1.49.0-nightly (2af662e22 2020-11-12)` or
- `rustc 1.50.0-nightly (1c389ffef 2020-11-24)` / `cargo 1.50.0-nightly (bfca1cd22 2020-11-24)`

`x86_64-pc-windows-gnu`

`cargo build` with dependencies or `cargo run` or `cargo test`
